  "title": "Augustine, Confessions §aug_conf_12_005: So that when thought seeketh what the sense may conceive under this, and sait...",
  "body": "So that when thought seeketh what the sense may conceive under this, and saith to itself, \"It is no intellectual form, as life, or justice; because it is the matter of bodies; nor object of sense, because being invisible, and without form, there was in it no object of sight or sense\";--while man's thought thus saith to itself, it may endeavour either to know it, by being ignorant of it; or to be ignorant, by knowing it.",
